The paper discusses a scheme for inferring labels of unlabeled data, which is a common problem in machine learning applications. The paper proposes a new method called GSAL, which uses supervised models to partition the data and avoid reliance on unsupervised clustering methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
